# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# free-claude-code — recommended per-tier routing (free-only)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This is a REFERENCE. You don't hand-edit free-claude-code's managed file —
# you enter these values in its Admin UI (Validate -> Apply). See config/README.md.
#
# Strategy: capable model on the tiers that think + make final edits,
# fast model on the Haiku tier for subagents/grunt work,
# a DIFFERENT provider as fallback so one rate-limit doesn't kill a session.

# Architect / hard reasoning + main coding (capable):
MODEL_OPUS=nvidia_nim/nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b
MODEL_SONNET=nvidia_nim/nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b

# Subagents + grunt work (fast):
MODEL_HAIKU=groq/llama-3.3-70b-versatile

# Fallback when a tier returns 429 — keep it on a provider different from the tiers above:
MODEL=open_router/openrouter/free

# Keys you'll paste into the Admin UI (free to obtain):
#   NVIDIA_NIM_API_KEY   -> https://build.nvidia.com/settings/api-keys
#   GROQ_API_KEY         -> https://console.groq.com/keys
#   OPENROUTER_API_KEY   -> https://openrouter.ai/keys

# Leave the 190k auto-compact window that fcc ships with ON — it stretches free quota.

# ── Local opt-in (if you ever have the RAM) ──
# Swap any tier to a local backend, e.g.:
#   MODEL_HAIKU=ollama/qwen2.5-coder
# free-claude-code already ships Ollama / LM Studio / llama.cpp — no extra code.
